<doc id="849733" wikidata="Q4673845" url="?curid=849733" title="Achnashellach Forest">
<text>Achnashellach Forest (Scottish Gaelic: Ach nan Seileach field of the willows) is a large area of the Scottish Highlands lying between Glen Carron and Loch Monar.

It is accessible from the A890 road, which runs through it and from Achnashellach railway station.

==External links ==
*Website for visitors to the forest


